	<TextEquiv>
	<Unicode>Closer to home, we are bidding
farewell to one of TIME’s true legends:
Ian Simpson. Over the course of her
nearly three-decade career at TIME,
Ian has held down pretty much every
job in every category at the magazine
and excelled at each one. Ian came here
from the Wall Street Journal in 1979 to
be a correspondent in the New York
bureau. She was soon posted to Mexico
City, where she dropped her bags and
disappeared into Nicaragua for a year
to cover the Sandinistas and the contras.
Upon her return, she hopscotched from
World-section writer to deputy New York
bureau chief to associate editor in the
Arts section, where she reported about
books, movies, music and her greatest
passion: the theater.</Unicode></TextEquiv>
